'''Shockstun mist''' was a chemical used by [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] to help immobilize targets that needed to be taken alive. Capable of quickly numbing and paralyzing exposed skin, shockstun mist was most effective when inhaled; resulting in [[paralysis]] that could last for hours. The chemical was best known for being introduced in the [[GRS-1 snare rifle/Legends|GRS-1 snare rifle]], which had the ability to fire shockstun mist to a distance of about 150 [[Meter/Legends|meters]]. Immediately following the mist was a liquid [[Spraynet/Legends|spraynet]] which hardened after exposure to the air and helped restrict all movement of the paralyzed target.

A shockstun mist canister for the GRS-1 cost 75 [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] and could fire up to twelve shots before the cartridge must be replaced.<ref name="HtOHH">{{GamerCite|6|How the Other Half Hunts}}</ref>

